*   **WGLC Status:** Both documents are considered feature-complete by the authors and chairs.

### 6. Post-Quantum EDHOC (Individual Drafts)
**Presentations:**
*   [09-10-Pocero-Updates on KEM-based Authentication methods for EDHOC](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-lake-updates-on-kem-based-authentication-methods-for-edhoc-00) - **Lydia Pocero**
*   [11-Papon-Post-Quantum EDHOC - Initiator and Responder using signature and/or KEM](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/125/materials/slides-125-lake-post-quantum-edhoc-initiator-and-responder-using-signature-andor-kem-00) - **Clément Papon**

*   **Approach:** Proposals for new EDHOC methods (4, 5, and 6) using KEMs for authentication to reduce the overhead of PQ signatures (e.g., Dilithium/ML-DSA).
*   **KEM Security:** Discussion on the need for CCA2-secure KEMs and protecting against re-encapsulation attacks.
*   **Analysis:** Preliminary Tamarin results show session key secrecy and agreement hold for these methods.

